Unfortunately it's exactly this type of response from many enchanters that causes them to defend charm so vocally. The truth is that charm needs to be fixed and that means nerfing the mages abilities equally in that arena. The fact that mages eventually get a high level charm is beside the point. I would certainly prefer that the mages limited charming ability retain <span style="font-style: italic">some </span> of it's resistance modifier because it is so limited, but in truth the fact that we get a charm at all is probably enough.
<br />

<br />
I'm not sure I feel that the changes are in the right direction though. Enchanters can still practically solo good loot giving mobs, and xp groups will still earn xp much faster with a charmed pet rather than with a tradtional group (even if a xp nerf is put in place). In groups where I'm with an enchanter with charmed pets I feel like I'm sneezing on mobs in comparison, and a group with an enchanter can do more than 2 groups without one can in some cases. These changes do little to adress that other than to make charm a bit more of a pain.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
